title: Football: Weather cancels, postpones games at the Shore
text:
Football: Weather cancels, postpones games at the Shore Chris Rotolo , @rote7123 10:12 p.m. EDT October 9, 2015 Lightning fills the sky over Borden Stadium in Rumson Friday evening, October 9, 2015, delaying the start of the Long Branch at Rumson-Fair Haven football game. (Photo: THOMAS P. COSTELLO) 8 CONNECT 1 TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
Though not a nor'easter or the remnants of Hurricane Joaquin, for the second consecutive week inclement weather interfered with Shore Conference football games causing postponements and cancellations. Week 5 coverage of high school football at the Shore 
The Week 5 meeting between non-divisional foes Toms River East and Freehold Township was set for Friday night, but due to rain, winds, and lightning was pushed back to a 1 p.m. start on Saturday at Freehold Township. The non-conference meeting between Old Bridge and Brick Memorial was also pushed back to Saturday at 1 p.m, as was the Class B South matchup featuring Donovan Catholic and Jackson Liberty. 
The anticipated Class A South meeting between Jackson Memorial and Toms River North suffered a wash out and is postponed until Saturday at 7 p.m. at Toms River. 
Earlier in the day, weather kept St. John Vianney from scoring any more points, as a lightning delay resulted in a cancellation of the second half, and the Lancers earning a 35-0 victory over Manchester. Don't miss a thing
